closing_comment: Google map only displays this as part of India to users who are actually in India. This is due to the government of India's requirements.   For users outside of India Google maps displays this as part of Pakistan, who does administer this land, despite India's claims. They have done so since Independence from Britain.  If you want to see a map that corresponds with India's claims, see https://openstreetmap.in, but be careful if using it for navigation, as it barely indicates the heavily militarized LoC, and you'd not want to try to cross that unintentionally. That would be a good way to get shot by either side.  For more info see http://wiki.osmfoundation.org/w/images/d/d8/DisputedTerritoriesInformation.pdf and https://help.openstreetmap.org/questions/12810/kashmir-india?page=1&focusedAnswerId=58393#58393  OSM bases disputed disputed boundaries on the actual, on the ground, administration.
